# P31 LABS — CURSOR RULES
# This file governs all code generation for the P31 ecosystem.

## IDENTITY
You are building P31 Labs' isomorphic ecosystem — an open-source assistive
technology platform for neurodivergent users. The visual identity is grounded
in real molecular geometry (Posner molecule Ca₉(PO₄)₆) and ³¹P NMR spectroscopy.

## DESIGN SYSTEM — NON-NEGOTIABLE
Colors (CSS custom properties, defined in src/styles/tokens.ts):
  --p31-void:          #050510     (background — never pure black)
  --p31-surface-1:     #0A0A1F
  --p31-surface-2:     #12122E
  --p31-surface-3:     #1A1A3E
  --p31-text:          #E0E0EE     (never pure white)
  --p31-text-dim:      #8888AA
  --p31-phosphor:      #00FF88     (primary accent — phosphor green)
  --p31-cyan:          #00D4FF     (quantum cyan)
  --p31-magenta:       #FF00CC     (neural magenta)
  --p31-violet:        #7A27FF     (quantum violet)
  --p31-amber:         #FFB000     (alerts/warnings — P3 phosphor)

Typography:
  - Monospace: "JetBrains Mono" for data, labels, system text
  - Display:   "Space Grotesk" for headings (wide, geometric)
  - Body:      "IBM Plex Sans" for readable paragraphs
  Font loading: Google Fonts via <link> in index.html

Visual rules:
  - Dark mode ONLY. No light theme. No white backgrounds.
  - Glow effects use layered box-shadow/text-shadow with accent colors
  - All 3D elements use additive blending for glow sprites
  - Transitions mimic FID (Free Induction Decay): fast attack, exponential decay
  - Scanline overlay available as a composable shader/CSS layer
  - Background particle fields for depth (never empty void)

## ARCHITECTURE
  - React + TypeScript + Vite
  - Three.js via React Three Fiber (R3F) — all 3D is declarative JSX
  - Zustand for global state (not Redux, not Context spam)
  - GLSL shaders imported via vite-plugin-glsl
  - Framer Motion for 2D UI transitions
  - Component-first: every visual element is a reusable component
  - File structure follows the molecular metaphor:
      src/
        atoms/       — smallest reusable pieces (buttons, badges, glows)
        molecules/   — composed components (cards, panels, nav clusters)
        organisms/   — full sections (dashboard views, 3D scenes)
        quantum/     — Three.js/R3F components (Posner, shaders, particles)
        copilot/     — voice/AI assistant logic
        store/       — Zustand stores
        styles/      — tokens, global CSS, shader utilities
        lib/         — pure utility functions

## CODE STYLE
  - TypeScript strict mode. No `any`.
  - Functional components only. No class components.
  - Custom hooks for all side effects (useThree, usePosner, useSpectrum, etc.)
  - Named exports (no default exports except page-level components)
  - Comments explain WHY, not WHAT. Reference the physics when relevant.
  - Shader code (.glsl/.frag/.vert) lives in src/quantum/shaders/

## ACCESSIBILITY (CRITICAL — THIS IS ASSISTIVE TECHNOLOGY)
  - All interactive elements keyboard-navigable
  - ARIA labels on non-obvious elements
  - Reduced-motion media query respected everywhere
  - Color alone never conveys meaning — use shape + color
  - Voice/screen-reader descriptions for 3D visualizations
  - Sensory modes: quiet mode (no animation), calm mode (reduced glow)

## DO NOT
  - Use light backgrounds, white themes, or Material Design
  - Import moment.js (use date-fns or native Intl)
  - Use Create React App patterns
  - Add unnecessary dependencies without justification
  - Use Lorem Ipsum — all placeholder text should reference P31 science
  - Ignore the void aesthetic — EVERY component lives on dark backgrounds
  - Use military, naval, or submarine metaphors in ANY copy or comments
